articles.description: Kelan Martin made three 3-pointers and scored 19 points and Butler ended a three-game losing streak with a 69-54 victory over Providence on Saturday.
articles.headline: Martin scores 19; Butler beats Providence 69-54

articles.description: Justin Robinson scored 18 points, Nickeil Alexander-Walker added 14 and Virginia Tech blew out reeling Georgia Tech 76-56 on Saturday.
articles.headline: Robinson, Alexander-Walker spark Virginia Tech's blowout win

articles.description: Mo Lewis had career highs of 12 points and eight rebounds and Navy beat Boston University 62-48 on Saturday.
articles.headline: Lewis leads Navy past Boston University 62-48

articles.description: Tyus Battle overcame a poor shooting game by scoring six points in the final 86 seconds, and the Syracuse Orangemen's stingy zone helped them beat Miami 62-55 Saturday.
articles.headline: Battle helps Syracuse finish off Miami 62-55

images.caption: Miami's Lonnie Walker IV drives down the baseline and throws down an emphatic two-handed dunk.
images.name: Walker elevates for two-handed finish

articles.description: Dylan Osetkowski scored 21 points, Texas slowed national scoring leader Trae Young, and the Longhorns beat No. 23 Oklahoma 77-66 on Saturday to extend the Sooners' losing streak to five games.
articles.headline: Osetkowski scores 21 as Texas tops No. 23 Oklahoma 77-66
